definitions.definition: Any polymer of (same or different) amino acids joined via peptide bonds .
Any such polymer that is not folded into a secondary structure of a protein .
A small protein containing up to 100 amino acids ; see also oligopeptide .

main_definition: ( organic chemistry ) Any polymer of (same or different) amino acids joined via peptide bonds .
secondary_definitions: ( biochemistry ) Any such polymer that is not folded into a secondary structure of a protein .
( biochemistry ) A small protein containing up to 100 amino acids ; see also oligopeptide .
